+# Maintenance Mode Guide
+
+This guide explains how to enable and use maintenance mode for the site.
+
+## ‚ö†Ô∏è Security Warning
+
+**IMPORTANT**: The basic implementation with `VITE_MAINTENANCE_BYPASS_TOKEN` is **NOT SECURE** for production use.
+
+**Why?** All environment variables starting with `VITE_` are **bundled into the frontend JavaScript** and can be viewed by anyone:
+
+```javascript
+// Anyone can access this in browser console:
+console.log(import.meta.env.VITE_MAINTENANCE_BYPASS_TOKEN)
+```
+
+**For Production:** Use one of the secure methods described below:
+- ‚úÖ Backend token verification (recommended)
+- ‚úÖ IP allowlist on CDN/server level
+- ‚úÖ HTTP Basic Auth
+- ‚úÖ Cloudflare Access/Zero Trust
+
+**For Development/Staging:** The basic token method is fine.
+
+## Quick Start
+
+### Option 1: Environment Variable (Recommended)
+
+1. **Enable maintenance mode**:
+   ```bash
+   # In your .env file
+   VITE_MAINTENANCE_MODE="true"
+   ```
+
+2. **Rebuild the application**:
+   ```bash
+   npm run build
+   ```
+
+3. **Deploy** the new build
+
+### Option 2: Dynamic Toggle (No Rebuild Required)
+
+Use the maintenance guard with localStorage:
+
+```javascript
+// In browser console or admin panel
+localStorage.setItem('maintenanceMode', 'true')
+```
+
+Then reload the page.
+
+## How It Works
+
+### 1. Router Guard Approach
+
+The `maintenanceGuard` checks on every navigation:
+
+```
+User tries to navigate
+  ‚Üì
+Is maintenance mode enabled?
+  ‚Üì YES
+Can user bypass? (token/IP)
+  ‚Üì NO
+Redirect to /maintenance
+  ‚Üì YES
+Allow access
+```
+
+### 2. Integration Steps
+
+**Step 1**: Add maintenance route to router
+
+```javascript
+// src/router/index.js
+const MaintenanceView = () => import('../views/MaintenanceView.vue')
+
+routes: [
+  { path: '/maintenance', name: 'maintenance', component: MaintenanceView },
+  // ... other routes
+]
+```
+
+**Step 2**: Add the guard
+
+```javascript
+// src/router/index.js
+import { maintenanceGuard } from './maintenanceGuard'
+
+// After creating router
+router.beforeEach(maintenanceGuard)
+```
+
+**Step 3**: Configure environment
+
+```bash
+# .env
+VITE_MAINTENANCE_MODE="false"
+VITE_MAINTENANCE_BYPASS_TOKEN="your-secret-token"
+```
+
+## Bypass Maintenance Mode
+
+### Method 1: Query Parameter
+
+Access the site with bypass token in URL:
+
+```
+https://yoursite.com/?bypass=your-secret-token
+```
+
+This will save the token to localStorage for the session.
+
+### Method 2: Direct localStorage
+
+In browser console:
+
+```javascript
+localStorage.setItem('maintenanceBypassToken', 'your-secret-token')
+```
+
+### Method 3: IP Allowlist (Requires server-side)
+
+```bash
+# .env
+VITE_MAINTENANCE_ALLOWED_IPS="192.168.1.1,10.0.0.1"
+```
+
+## Alternative: API-Controlled Maintenance
+
+For dynamic control from Payload CMS without rebuild:
+
+### 1. Add to Settings Global
+
+```typescript
+// cms/src/globals/Settings.ts
+{
+  name: 'maintenanceMode',
+  type: 'group',
+  fields: [
+    {
+      name: 'enabled',
+      type: 'checkbox',
