+```
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+**Issue**: Maintenance page shows for everyone, can't bypass
+
+**Solution**: Check bypass token in .env matches URL parameter
+
+---
+
+**Issue**: Changes to VITE_MAINTENANCE_MODE don't work
+
+**Solution**: Must rebuild app (`npm run build`) for env changes
+
+---
+
+**Issue**: Want instant toggle without rebuild
+
+**Solution**: Use API-controlled approach or CDN-level redirect
+
+## Security Best Practices
+
+### ‚ö†Ô∏è Critical Security Issues
+
+1. **Frontend tokens are NOT secure**
+   - `VITE_*` environment variables are PUBLIC in compiled JavaScript
+   - Anyone can find the bypass token in browser DevTools
+   - **DO NOT use for production maintenance mode**
+
+2. **Secure Alternatives for Production**
+
+   **Option A: Backend Token Verification** (Recommended)
+   - Store token only in backend environment
+   - Frontend sends token to API for verification
+   - See `maintenanceGuard.secure.js` for implementation
+   - Requires Payload CMS endpoints (see `cms/src/endpoints/maintenance.example.ts`)
+
+   **Option B: IP Allowlist**
+   - Configure on CDN level (Cloudflare, Vercel, Netlify)
+   - No tokens exposed to client
+   - Best for teams with static IPs
+
+   **Option C: HTTP Basic Auth**
+   - Built into browsers
+   - Configure on server/CDN level
+   - Simple username/password prompt
+
+   **Option D: Cloudflare Access**
+   - Enterprise-grade authentication
+   - SSO integration available
+   - Free tier available
+
+3. **Security Checklist**
+   - [ ] Never commit `.env` file with real tokens
+   - [ ] Use secure method for production (backend verification or IP allowlist)
+   - [ ] Basic token method OK for dev/staging only
+   - [ ] Use HTTPS always
+   - [ ] Rotate any exposed tokens immediately
+   - [ ] Consider time-limited tokens (expire after X hours)
+   - [ ] Use `sessionStorage` instead of `localStorage` (cleared on browser close)
+   - [ ] Implement rate limiting on bypass verification endpoint
+
+4. **If Token is Exposed**
+   - Immediately rotate the token in backend environment
+   - Redeploy backend with new token
+   - Clear sessions/cookies for all users
+   - Check access logs for unauthorized access
+
+### Development vs Production
+
+**Development/Staging:**
+- Basic `VITE_MAINTENANCE_BYPASS_TOKEN` is acceptable
+- Risk is minimal (non-production data)
+- Convenience over security
+
+**Production:**
+- **NEVER** use frontend-exposed tokens
+- Use backend verification or CDN-level protection
+- Implement proper authentication
+- Log all bypass attempts
