+```
+
+---
+
+## FAQ
+
+**Q: Can I use frontend token for production?**
+A: No. It's visible in compiled JavaScript. Anyone can bypass it.
+
+**Q: What's the quickest secure method?**
+A: IP allowlist on CDN level (Cloudflare, Vercel).
+
+**Q: Do I need Payload CMS for backend verification?**
+A: No. Any backend (Node.js, PHP, Python) works. Payload example provided for convenience.
+
+**Q: Can I test maintenance mode locally?**
+A: Yes. Set `VITE_MAINTENANCE_MODE="true"` and use bypass token.
+
+**Q: How to revoke compromised token?**
+A: Backend method: Change env var, restart server. Frontend method: Must rebuild app.
+
+---
+
+## Recommendations
+
+### For Your Portfolio Site
+
+**Development:**
+‚úÖ Current implementation (frontend token) is fine
+
+**Production:**
+I recommend **Backend Token Verification** because:
+1. You're already using Payload CMS (easy to add endpoints)
+2. Flexible - can toggle without rebuild
+3. Can share time-limited tokens with client
+4. Most secure while staying simple
+
+**Fallback:**
+If backend isn't ready, use **Cloudflare Page Rule** with static HTML:
+- Instant activation
+- No rebuild needed
+- Free on Cloudflare
+
+---
+
